input_str: One of the fun things about covering so many different areas of science is that you often come across things you had no idea existed. This week's discovery goes by the name of "diffuse interstellar bands," a phenomenon first discovered back in the 1920s. Since then, dozens of these DIBs, which represent areas of the spectrum that are absorbed by the interstellar medium, have been discovered.
